6 amount used to recompute the retirement benefit exceed Forty
7 Thousand Dollars ($40,000.00). The adjusted retirement benefit
8 amount required by this section shall be the amount used for
9 computation of any cost-of-living adjustment which becomes effective
10 for the first time on or after the effective date of this act. The
11 provisions of this section shall not authorize the payment of any
12 benefit amount retroactively and any increase in the retirement
13 benefit amount resulting from the recomputation of the average
14 salary required by this section shall only be applicable on or after
15 the effective date of this act.
16 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2025.
17 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
18 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
19 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
20 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
